'''King Claudius Remanis''' was once a ruler of [[Varrock]], the capital city of the [[kingdom]] of [[Misthalin]]. Although the time of his rule is unknown, it is believed he lived some time in the [[Fourth Age]]. He does not appear in-game, but is mentioned in issue 4 of [[Postbag from the Hedge]].

According to [[Duke Horacio]] of [[Lumbridge]], King Claudius granted his (Duke Horacio's) ancestor [[Duke Polonius|Polonius]] the title of duke in exchange for his service as a {{WP|vassal}} in the service of Misthalin. Polonius would later go on to establish [[Lumbridge Castle]] in the place of a wooden fort that had previously served as a lone defensive structure. His position of duke was later passed on through the generations.{{CitePostbag|issue=4|letter=Letter 3|author=Duke Horacio}}

==Trivia==
*Claudius and Polonius are names from the Shakespeare play, {{WP|Hamlet}}.

